data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both compiled and ran without issues on .NET 11 (preview). You can write:

```csharp
Span<nint>  a = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> b = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

One minor caveat: `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since the size isn't known at compile time), but you can use `nint.Size` instead. On this 64-bit system, `nint` is 8 bytes.
